# 5️⃣ If interviewer asks your project

You can say:

> In my project, I evaluated the model using **accuracy, precision, recall, and F1 score**, but in medical diagnosis **recall is especially important because missing a disease case (false negative) can be critical**.

2) Why is accuracy not enough for medical diagnosis?

Accuracy alone is not always reliable in medical problems because the dataset may be imbalanced. For example, if most images are normal, a model could predict “normal” most of the time and still get high accuracy.
Therefore, we also use precision, recall, and F1-score to better evaluate the model’s performance.
